Installation Instructions for STACCATO
You have to specify location of your CUDD `include` dirrectory in CMakeLists.txt
As static library: 
$> cmake . -DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS=OFF
$> make

As shared library:
Make sure that you have built CUDD as a shared library and that
it is installed in /usr/local/lib/libcudd.so or to another location specified
by using the CUDD_DIR environment variable.
$> cmake . -DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS=ON
$> make


Dependencies:
  CUDD >= 2.4.1 
  (Edit the INCLUDE path in the Makefile to include the appropriate CUDD headers)
  
  gcc 3.4, 4.1, 4.2, 4.3 or 4.4
